issue.title: Geocoding postal code type
issue.body:
### Description

Jim Barry brought to my attention that the postal code parameter should be wrapped in quotes as it is an alphanumeric value. Issues arise when using a postal code starting with zero as demonstrated in these CodePen examples ([ex1](https://codepen.io/cyatteau/pen/OJoYRNr), [ex2](https://codepen.io/cyatteau/pen/BaOeRLj)). 

Several places state or use a _number_ instead of a _string_, which need to be addressed:
- [ ] The [API Reference](https://developers.arcgis.com/arcgis-rest-js/api-reference/arcgis-rest-geocoding/IGeocodeOptions#postal) states that the postal code value should be a _number_.
- [ ] The example given [here](https://developers.arcgis.com/arcgis-rest-js/api-reference/arcgis-rest-geocoding/geocode).
- [ ] The tutorial [here](https://developers.arcgis.com/arcgis-rest-js/geocode-and-search/search-for-an-address/).

### Link to page

https://developers.arcgis.com/arcgis-rest-js/api-reference/arcgis-rest-geocoding/IGeocodeOptions#postal

issue.title: Update automated unit tests to run on Node 20
issue.body:
### Describe the problem

Node v20 is now the current active LTS version:
https://github.com/nodejs/release#release-schedule

![image](https://github.com/Esri/arcgis-rest-js/assets/137905994/c5e65a5b-7988-46d4-bb8c-7006f998d4d7)


### Describe the proposed solution

So we should probably add v20 to the list of versions that we automatically test on:

https://github.com/Esri/arcgis-rest-js/blob/9ec89a2113dd616519398cc217309930fed7c7bc/.github/workflows/pull-request-tests.yml#L21

### Alternatives considered

_No response_

### Additional Information

Questions:

- Should we also remove Node 14 from the automated unit tests ([end of life](https://github.com/nodejs/release#end-of-life-releases) was 2023-04-30)?
- Should we also remove Node 16 from the automated unit tests ([end of life](https://github.com/nodejs/release#end-of-life-releases) was 2023-09-11)?

issue.title: Provide option to force `/addItem` request to use `form-data` content type
issue.body:
### Describe the problem

In the last step of creating a Survey123 report, we utilize [`/addItem`](https://developers.arcgis.com/rest/users-groups-and-items/add-item.htm) to add the generated report file (.docx or .pdf) as an item. Since the report file already exists in S3 bucket, we use `dataUrl` property and send the request in `x-www-form-urlencoded` type to let portal download the file instead of uploading a binary file in `form-data` type. This works for most cases.

However, it turns out that some user's web application firewall rejects the `/addItem` request if the request is send in `x-www-form-urlencoded` type AND there are any HTML contents (e.g. `<a>` tag in item's `description` property) in the request.

### Describe the proposed solution

Provide an option to send the `/addItem` request, even all POST requests, as `form-data` content type even no binary file in the request.

### Alternatives considered

_No response_

### Additional Information

Similar to https://github.com/Esri/arcgis-rest-js/issues/499

comment.body: Ok thanks for the info. Since this is a specific firewall setting, it doesn't seem like that should be a general change that should be applied for everyone who uses ArcGIS REST JS. So I'll close this for now but if others have similar issues please log here.

issue.title: Provide option to force `/addItem` request to use `form-data` content type
issue.body:
### Describe the problem

In the last step of creating a Survey123 report, we utilize [`/addItem`](https://developers.arcgis.com/rest/users-groups-and-items/add-item.htm) to add the generated report file (.docx or .pdf) as an item. Since the report file already exists in S3 bucket, we use `dataUrl` property and send the request in `x-www-form-urlencoded` type to let portal download the file instead of uploading a binary file in `form-data` type. This works for most cases.

However, it turns out that some user's web application firewall rejects the `/addItem` request if the request is send in `x-www-form-urlencoded` type AND there are any HTML contents (e.g. `<a>` tag in item's `description` property) in the request.

### Describe the proposed solution

Provide an option to send the `/addItem` request, even all POST requests, as `form-data` content type even no binary file in the request.

### Alternatives considered

_No response_

### Additional Information

Similar to https://github.com/Esri/arcgis-rest-js/issues/499

comment.body:
Hi @gavinr-maps , the problem was caused by the Firewall settings in the client's Enterprise deployment, which might be an intentional setting. We confirmed this issue by doing a minimum test in Postman: as long as we change `x-www-form-urlencoded` to `form-data` and keep all other parameters unchanged, the `/addItem` request succeeded.

The workaround fix in the Survey123 report service code currently only changes `x-www-form-urlencoded` to `form-data` when sending the specific `/addItem` request, which also fixed the report workflow for this client's environment.

![image](https://github.com/Esri/arcgis-rest-js/assets/7665168/df492dc7-a670-48b2-b5b3-6cdd5c9b908c)
